01/08/2008
ATHENS, Greece -- A newly emerged terrorist group claimed responsibility for three bombings in Greece between 2004 and 2008, media reported on Thursday (July 31st).
The organisation, which calls itself Popular Will, sent a statement to the daily Eleftherotypia on Wednesday.
The group said it was responsible for bombing a courthouse in the central town of Larissa in 2004, slightly injuring a bystander.
Popular Will also claimed responsibility for two attempted bombings in Athens -- against the offices of the German pharmaceutical Bayer in June 2007 and against the Economic and Social Committee of Greece this past Tuesday.
(Ta nea, Eleftherotypia, In.news, SKAI, AP - 31/07/08)
